sven meinhardt (born september 28, 1971 in mülheim an der ruhr, nordrhein-westfalen) is a former field hockey forward from germany, who won the gold medal with the men's national team at the 1992 summer olympics in barcelona, spain. a player from htc uhlenhorst in mülheim an der ruhr, he was also on the side that competed at the 1996 summer olympics in atlanta, united states.